sentences: Fred Albin (December 11, 1903 – May 3, 1968) was an American sound engineer.

He also won the Academy Award for Technical Achievement that year along with Thomas T. Moulton and the Sound Department of the Samuel Goldwyn Studio for the origination and application of the Delta db test for sound recording in motion pictures.
